# Folder Structure — mirror ybala-customer-app

Keep the same top-level folders and file-placement conventions as
`/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/ybala-customer-app`. Do not invent new
top-level folders or alternate layouts.

```
app/            # Expo Router screens (file-based routing)
  (auth)/       # Auth stack (grouped route)
  (tabs)/       # Bottom tab navigator (grouped route)
  _layout.tsx   # Root layout — providers, nav handler, ToastContainer
  index.tsx     # Root redirect
components/     # Reusable components; feature subfolders (e.g. Home/, Menu/)
  ui/           # UI primitives (Input, Button, ...) exported via index.ts
constants/      # colors.ts, config.ts
hooks/          # TanStack Query hooks, one per concern; barrel index.ts
providers/      # QueryProvider, AuthProvider, ...
services/       # api.ts (publicApi/protectedApi) + one <domain>Service.ts each; index.ts
storage/        # secure.ts (token storage)
store/          # Zustand stores, one per domain: <domain>.store.ts
types/          # Types split per domain + barrel index.ts
utils/          # errorExtractor, toast, index.ts helpers
```

## Rules

- One store per domain in `store/` named `<domain>.store.ts`.
- One service per domain in `services/` named `<domain>Service.ts`, all built on
  `publicApi` / `protectedApi` from `services/api.ts`.
- Data fetching lives in `hooks/` as React Query hooks, never inline in screens.
- Screen route files go under `app/`; shared UI goes under `components/`
  (screen-specific pieces in a feature subfolder).
- Reusable primitives live in `components/ui/` and are re-exported from
  `components/ui/index.ts`.
- When a folder/file exists in the customer app for the same concern, match its
  name and location exactly.
